column69:
Training inside the hospital is not compulsory or not of the highest quality and is very difficult to have supervision for patients. Even though they are starting to organize it better, as a 4th year resident I couldn't benefit from the changes that are taking place just now. 
On the other hand a proper training is always offered through universities and is excellent, but is very expensive and sometimes is the reason we don't do it.

column25: I think any professional working in mental health should have a minimum training in psychotherapy, I particularly prefer a psychodinamic ground in which you can add any interest you have as I do with familiar therapy and group therapy. Usually I have found interesting combine it with a body-oriented therapy in order to release emotion that can be blocked.
